    "story":  [
                  "At the very summit, \u003cb\u003eQuince\u003c/b\u003e is grinding out 6 clean sheets like a man morally opposed to fun \u0026mdash; ugly, effective, and a touch boring. Hot on their heels, \u003cb\u003eBig Pewerk\u003c/b\u003e bagged the pasting of the tournament so far, Netherlands (beautiful football, then a fistfight among themselves) romping home 5-1. Borderline rude. Rounding out the smug end of the table, \u003cb\u003eSid\u003c/b\u003e is the undisputed sultan of the stalemate: 5 draws and counting. Edge-of-the-seat stuff it is not.",
                  "Wading into the midtable swamp, \u003cb\u003eEllie\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s lot have collectively decided defending is for cowards \u0026mdash; 24 goals banged in (GD +1), spearheaded by Germany (ruthlessly, tediously efficient). Keeping them grim company, \u003cb\u003eElsa\u003c/b\u003e is hauling Tunisia (stubborn, organised, impossible to love) around like a dead fridge up a fire escape \u0026mdash; it\u0027s played, and contributed the square root of sod all. And clinging on by their fingernails, \u003cb\u003eIke\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s backline has the structural integrity of a wet paper bag \u0026mdash; 18 shipped already, with Uzbekistan (the tournament\u0027s great unmarked mystery box) alone waving in 8.",
                  "Down in the cheap seats, \u003cb\u003eMurray\u003c/b\u003e watched Czechia (lanky set-piece menaces) get taken to the absolute cleaners 0-3 \u0026mdash; a scoreline best discussed in hushed, pitying tones. And scraping the very bottom of the barrel, \u003cb\u003eEtan\u003c/b\u003e has spread the love like a sensible little pension fund \u0026mdash; 5 teams all chipping in, not a single passenger. Boringly effective."
              ],
